issue.title: When I open a non https site the function globalThis.crypto.randomUUID() is called, but that does not exists
issue.body:
## Description
The http://mypc:4400/somesite/duckduckgo-privacy-protection.js?scope=injectfirefox script has a call to `globalThis.crypto.randomUUID()` however because the site (in this case some local site), is accessed over http, this function is not supported.

## Steps to Reproduce
<!-- How can we reproduce the bug ourselves -->
1. open the console in firefox
2. visit http://httpforever.com/

**Expected behavior:**
No errors
<!-- What you expect to happen -->

**Actual behavior:**
<!-- What actually happens -->
TypeError: globalThis.crypto.randomUUID is not a function inject.js:2648:54


**Versions**

<!--
To find the extension versions:
     Firefox: go to about:addons in the address bar, click DuckDuckGo Privacy Essentials, version is toward the bottom of the page.

     Chrome: go to about:extensions in the address bar, click "details" on DuckDuckGo Privacy Essentials, the version is listed near the top of the page.
-->

- Extension: 2023.10.12
- Browser:  Firefox 119.0 (x64)
- OS: Windows 11

## Additional Information
1. Is the issue repeatable or intermittent? repeatable 
2. Did this issue start after an upgrade to a new extension version? I do not know, I just noticed the error a couple of days ago.
3. Are there any errors in the extension debugging console? Yes, that is the thingy
4. Include screenshots if they're helpful.

comment.body: Owh to be clear, this function should not be called on http sites, it is not supported on http sites

pull_request.title: Bump the external-dependencies group with 2 updates
pull_request.body:
Bumps the external-dependencies group with 2 updates: [fake-indexeddb](https://github.com/dumbmatter/fakeIndexedDB) and [sass](https://github.com/sass/dart-sass). Updates `fake-indexeddb` from 5.0.0 to 5.0.1
Release notes

Sourced from fake-indexeddb's releases.

v5.0.1

  • #89 - Fixed bug where ArrayBuffer views were not being correctly handled when used as keys.

  • #88 - Added explanation to README.md about how to use fake-indexeddb v5+ with jsdom, since a structuredClone polyfill is not included anymore.

Changelog

Sourced from fake-indexeddb's changelog.

5.0.1 (2023-10-25)

  • #89 - Fixed bug where ArrayBuffer views were not being correctly handled when used as keys.

  • #88 - Added explanation to README.md about how to use fake-indexeddb v5+ with jsdom, since a structuredClone polyfill is not included anymore.

Commits
  • b5a7cb2 5.0.1
  • f34137c Changelog
  • cdcb99c Update README for jsdom compatibility with fake-indexeddb 5
  • 26b6d8c Follow spec better when converting ArrayBuffer views to keys
  • See full diff in compare view

See the full changelog for changes in earlier releases.
